About
Catch the emotionally-charged Michael Jackson ONE by Cirque Du Soleil at Las Vegas’ Mandalay Bay Resort and Casino. Helmed by a talented cast of acrobats, dancers, and performers who put their heart and soul into honoring MJ’s legacy, the show is a seamless visual extravaganza that’s driven by his greatest hits. Expect a medley of aerial performances, acrobatics, and riveting choreography that offer a fitting tribute to the acclaimed singer. Standard tickets or V.I.P. packages are available, which include early access, a pre-show reception, a guided virtual tour, artist meet and greet, and exclusive seats. – Tripadvisor
Duration: 1-2 hours

  • Steve K
    4 contributions
    Real Entertainment!
    There were so many kinds of entertainment here, it's hard to focus on "the show". Michael Jackson One show at Mandalay Bay was a real top level production. Some music from MJ that I hadn't heard previously, and the talent and performance was well choreographed and sequenced. Amazing acrobatics and talented dancers. Some loud parts, family friendly though. We had seats 'upstairs' but they were essentially at the same level as the last row of the 'downstairs' seating - so the seats were quite a bit less expensive. Perfect as far as sightlines go. No real need to ante up for the most expensive seats in the house unless you really need to be close up. Because there's so much going on during the show, it was great to be able to see the entire stage - and since the cast uses the entire theater as part of their stage - the ability to see what's coming in from above and down the aisles makes a much better viewing situation. Sitting any closer and we'd have missed quite a bit of what was going on in the show. To be clear, almost the entire theater is the stage.
    Visited March 2024
    Traveled with family
    Written March 26, 2024
